  "local_port": 48012,
  "remote_port": 443,
  "prompt": "Where do we get beef jerky or biltong in London?",
  "response": "In London, you can find **beef jerky** (a thinly sliced, smoked dried meat, often associated with the US) and **biltong** (a thicker, air-dried South African variant, typically cured with vinegar and spices) at various locations. Here\u2019s a curated guide:\n\n---\n\n### **1. Specialty Stores & Butchers**\n- **The Savanna** (Fulham)  \n  A South African shop specializing in biltong, dro\u00ebwors, and other cured meats.  \n  **Address:** 735 Fulham Road, SW6 5UU.\n\n- **The Ginger Pig** (Multiple locations)  \n  High-quality butchers offering their own **beef jerky** (sometimes with chili or honey flavors).  \n  **Locations:** Marylebone, Borough Market, Hackney, etc.\n\n- **The Butchery** (Belgravia)  \n  Artisanal meats, including house-made jerky.  \n  **Address:** 39 Elizabeth Street, SW1W 9RP.\n\n---\n\n### **2. Supermarkets & Health Food Stores**\n- **Waitrose & Marks & Spencer**  \n  Look for jerky in the snack aisles (e.g., **\"Wild West\"** or **\"Percy Pig\"** jerky brands).\n\n- **Planet Organic**  \n  Stock healthier jerky options (organic, gluten-free brands like **\"Oomi\"**).\n\n- **Whole Foods Market** (Kensington)  \n  Carries US-style jerky and sometimes biltong.\n\n---\n\n### **3. Markets & Street Food**\n- **Borough Market**  \n  Check stalls like **Turnips** for artisanal jerky or biltong vendors on weekends.\n\n- **Maltby Street Market**  \n  Occasional South African vendors selling fresh biltong.\n\n- **Camden Market**  \n  International snack stalls may stock jerky.\n\n---\n\n### **4. Dedicated South African Shops**\n- **Springbok Foods** (Clapham)  \n  Offers biltong, boerewors, and South African snacks.  \n  **Address:** 41 Clapham High Street, SW4 7TG.\n\n- **The South African Shop** (Online & Clapham)  \n  Delivers biltong nationwide, with pickup in Clapham.  \n  **Website:** thesouthafricanshop.co.uk.\n\n---\n\n### **5. Online Retailers**\n- **Biltong.co.uk** or **Biltong Chief**  \n  Specialize in authentic South African biltong (next-day London delivery).\n\n- **Jawbox Jerky**  \n  UK-based jerky brand with creative flavors (e.g., bourbon, teriyaki).\n\n- **Snogdales**  \n  Award-winning British jerky, available online.\n\n---\n\n### **6. Vegan Options**\n- **Vegan Biltong**  \n  Available at **Whole Foods** or online via **The Vegan Biltong Co.**\n\n- **Sgaia Foods**  \n  Plant-based \"mheat\" jerky, sold at health stores.\n\n---\n\n### **Tips**\n- Check **South African expat hubs** like Fulham or Clapham for niche shops.\n- Use delivery apps (**Deliveroo**, **Uber Eats**) for quick orders from specialty stores.\n- Local butchers may prepare jerky/biltong on request\u2014call ahead!\n\nWhether you crave smoky US-style jerky or vinegary South African biltong, London\u2019s diverse food scene has you covered! \ud83c\udf0d\ud83c\udf56",
